RACE.RACE_TEXT: SUFFOLK DOWNS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 9300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of two races at a mile or over since July 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Such a race since June 4 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THIS ONES FOR NINA rushed to gain command into the first turn, set a pressured pace, avoided the trouble near the eighth pole and prevailed in a long drive under strong urging. DANCE TO THE ROAR was forwardly placed four-wide, rallied into the stretch, was guided left to close a hole in the upper stretch, then was bumped twice by IRISH BEAU, and finished well. IRISH BEAU went five-wide on the first turn, angled inside near the half-mile pole, was blocked behind and beside rivals from the three-eighths pole, tried to split rivals three-wide in the upper stretch, alternated bumping MAJESTIC DESERT and DANCE TO THE ROAR each twice, angled out and finished well. MAJESTIC DESERT pressed the pace three-wide on the first turn, dueled between rivals on the second turn, was bumped hard twice near the eighth pole and weakened. LORDS IMAGE went six-wide pressing the pace on the first turn and was outrun. BUGSY LOSTY dueled between rivals on the first turn and was through after three furlongs. LIKE A BOSS reared at the start and trailed, had a strong rally from the nine-sixteenth pole to the three-sixteenths pole and gave way, AFTER THE STEWARDS POSTED THE INQUIRY SIGN AND REVIEWED THE START AND THE STRETCH BUMPING AND THE RIDER OF MAJESTIC DESERT CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF IRISH BEAU, ALLEGING INTERFERENCE THROUGH THE STRETCH, THE RESULT WAS ALLOWED TO STAND.
